1
00:00:23,216 --> 00:00:25,326
I'm talkin'about friendship.

2
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:27,724
I'm talkin'about character.

3
00:00:28,011 --> 00:00:32,039
I'm talkin'about--
Hell, Leo, I ain't embarrassed
to use the word.

4
00:00:32,231 --> 00:00:35,108
I'm talkin' about ethics.

5
00:00:35,396 --> 00:00:37,314
You know I'm a sportin' man.

6
00:00:37,410 --> 00:00:39,712
I like to lay the occasional bet.

7
00:00:39,808 --> 00:00:42,205
But I ain't that sportin'.

8
00:00:42,397 --> 00:00:45,083
When I fix a fight--
Say I pay a three to one favorite...

9
00:00:45,179 --> 00:00:47,097
to throw a goddamned fight.

10
00:00:47,193 --> 00:00:51,029
I figure I got the right
to expect that fight
to go off at three to one.

11
00:00:51,317 --> 00:00:54,674
But every time I lay in bed
with this son of a bitch
Bernie Bernbaum,

12
00:00:54,866 --> 00:00:57,935
before I know it,
the odds is even up.

13
00:00:58,127 --> 00:01:00,525
Or worse, I'm bettin'
on the short money.

14
00:01:00,716 --> 00:01:02,730
The sheeny knows
I like sure things.

15
00:01:02,922 --> 00:01:06,087
He's sellin' the information
I fixed the fight.

16
00:01:06,279 --> 00:01:08,485
Out of town money
comes pouring in.

17
00:01:08,581 --> 00:01:10,691
The odds go straight to hell.

18
00:01:10,882 --> 00:01:13,951
I don't know who
he's sellin' to-- maybe
the Los Angeles combine.

19
00:01:14,047 --> 00:01:15,870
I don't know. The point is,

20
00:01:16,061 --> 00:01:19,898
Bernie ain't satisfied
with the honest dollar
he can make off the vig.

21
00:01:20,089 --> 00:01:23,063
He ain't satisfied with
the business I do on his book.

22
00:01:23,254 --> 00:01:25,940
He is sellin' tips on how I bet.

23
00:01:26,132 --> 00:01:29,105
And that means part
of the payoff that should
be riding on my hip...

24
00:01:29,296 --> 00:01:31,215
is riding on someone else's.

25
00:01:31,406 --> 00:01:33,708
So, back we go
to these questions--

26
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:37,448
friendship, character,

27
00:01:37,736 --> 00:01:39,846
ethics.

28
00:01:42,915 --> 00:01:44,833
So, it's clear what I'm saying?

29
00:01:46,272 --> 00:01:48,861
As mud.

30
00:01:51,547 --> 00:01:56,823
It's gettin' so a businessman
can't expect no return
from a fixed fight.

31
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:00,275
Now, if you can't trust a fix,
what can you trust?

32
00:02:00,467 --> 00:02:03,536
For a good return,you gotta
go bettin'on chance,

33
00:02:03,824 --> 00:02:05,838
and then you're
back with anarchy.

34
00:02:06,030 --> 00:02:07,756
Right back in the jungle.

35
00:02:07,948 --> 00:02:12,647
That's why ethics is important--
what separates us
from the animals,

36
00:02:12,839 --> 00:02:15,141
the beasts of burden,
the beasts of prey.

37
00:02:15,332 --> 00:02:17,155
Ethics.

38
00:02:17,251 --> 00:02:21,087
Whereas, uh, Bernie Bernbaum
is a horse of a different color,

39
00:02:21,279 --> 00:02:24,731
ethics-wise, as in
he ain't got any.

40
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:28,759
- You sure it's Bernie
selling you out?
- It ain't elves.

41
00:02:29,047 --> 00:02:32,596
- No one else knows about the fix?
- No one that ain't got ethics.

42
00:02:32,691 --> 00:02:35,473
What about the fighters
you pay to tank out?

43
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:39,405
We only pick fighters
we know we can put
the fear of God in.

44
00:02:39,597 --> 00:02:41,707
Any other bookies know?
You play anyone else's book?

45
00:02:41,803 --> 00:02:44,776
I-I lay an occasional bet
with Mink Larouie.

46
00:02:45,063 --> 00:02:47,365
- But it ain't Mink.
I'll vouch for that.
-How do you know?

47
00:02:47,557 --> 00:02:50,530
It ain't Mink.
Mink is Eddie Dane's boy.

48
00:02:50,722 --> 00:02:54,271
Of course the Dane
always knows about the fix.

49
00:02:54,463 --> 00:02:56,477
And what the hell
is that supposed to mean?

50
00:02:56,669 --> 00:02:59,834
Let it drift. All it means is
a lot of people know.

51
00:03:00,026 --> 00:03:02,232
I guess you ain't
been listenin'.

52
00:03:02,328 --> 00:03:04,342
Sure, other people know.

53
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:07,027
That's why we gotta go
to this question of character...

54
00:03:07,219 --> 00:03:10,575
to determine just who, exactly,
is chiselin' in on my fix.

55
00:03:10,863 --> 00:03:14,316
And that's how we know
that it's Bernie Bernbaum,
the shmatte kid--

56
00:03:14,508 --> 00:03:17,289
'cause ethically,
he's kinda shaky.

57
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:22,372
- So you want to kill him.
- For starters.

58
00:03:36,470 --> 00:03:40,594
Sorry, Caspar.
Bernie pays for protection.

59
00:03:42,225 --> 00:03:45,102
Listen, Leo, I ain't
askin' you for permission.

60
00:03:45,294 --> 00:03:49,130
I'm tellin' you as a courtesy.
I need to do this thing,
so it's gonna get done.

61
00:03:49,418 --> 00:03:51,144
And I'm tellin' you, as
a courtesy, you'll have trouble.

62
00:03:51,336 --> 00:03:54,885
You came here to see if
I'd kick if you killed Bernie.
Well, there's your answer.

63
00:03:55,077 --> 00:03:58,530
I pay off to you every month
like a greengrocer

64
00:03:58,626 --> 00:04:00,448
a lot more than the shmatte,

65
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:02,462
and I'm sick of gettin'
the high hat.

66
00:04:02,558 --> 00:04:05,339
You pay off for protection
just like everyone else.

67
00:04:05,531 --> 00:04:08,120
As far as I know, and
what I don't know in this town
ain't worth knowing,

68
00:04:08,312 --> 00:04:10,134
the cops haven't closed
any of your dives...

69
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:12,532
and the D.A. hasn't touched
any of your rackets.

70
00:04:12,724 --> 00:04:15,025
You haven't bought any license
to kill bookies,

71
00:04:15,217 --> 00:04:17,040
and today I ain't sellin'any.

72
00:04:17,231 --> 00:04:19,917
So take your flunky and dangle.

73
00:04:20,013 --> 00:04:24,137
You think I'm some guinea
fresh off the boat,
and you can kick me.

74
00:04:24,328 --> 00:04:28,069
But I'm too big for that now.
I'm sick of takin'
the strap from you, Leo.

75
00:04:28,356 --> 00:04:30,562
I'm sick of marching
into this goddamn office...

76
00:04:30,658 --> 00:04:32,576
to kiss your Irish ass,

77
00:04:32,672 --> 00:04:34,974
and I'm sick of the high hat!

78
00:04:51,086 --> 00:04:54,060
You's fancy pants, all of youse.

79
00:04:55,978 --> 00:04:58,280
Johnny?

80
00:04:58,472 --> 00:05:01,541
You're exactly as big
as I let you be and no bigger,

81
00:05:01,637 --> 00:05:03,747
and don't forget it, ever.

82
00:05:06,336 --> 00:05:08,159
That's right, Leo.

83
00:05:08,254 --> 00:05:10,173
You're the big shot
around here,

84
00:05:10,364 --> 00:05:13,721
and I'm just some schnook
likes to get slapped around.

85
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:23,791
Twist a pig's ear,
watch him squeal.

86
00:05:32,135 --> 00:05:35,396
- Bad play, Leo.
- Who got up the wrong side, huh?

87
00:05:35,684 --> 00:05:38,272
-Same side as always.
- That's what I mean.
Still owe money to--

88
00:05:38,368 --> 00:05:41,629
Who is your bookie, Lazarre?
I could put it right for you.

89
00:05:41,821 --> 00:05:44,602
- Thanks, Leo. I don't need it.
- In a pig's eye.

90
00:05:44,794 --> 00:05:46,616
You haven't played
a winner in six weeks.

91
00:05:46,712 --> 00:05:48,918
People will speak ill of me
if I let him break your legs.

92
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:52,658
- People will say I had it coming.
-And they'll be right,
but that ain't the point.

93
00:05:52,851 --> 00:05:56,399
Call me a bighearted slob,
but I'm gonna square it
for you, yeah.

94
00:05:56,687 --> 00:05:59,852
I think I'll do that
this very same night.

95
00:05:59,948 --> 00:06:03,592
Lookin' at you mopin' around
takes away all my--

96
00:06:03,784 --> 00:06:06,182
What do you call it?
"Joy de veever"?

97
00:06:06,374 --> 00:06:09,251
-Joie de vivre.
- Well, if you're gonna
laugh at me, the hell with ya.

98
00:06:09,347 --> 00:06:11,744
The hell with you.

99
00:06:12,032 --> 00:06:14,238
I'll square myself with Lazarre,
if you don't mind.

100
00:06:14,430 --> 00:06:17,115
That's why God invented cards.

101
00:06:19,609 --> 00:06:22,198
- There is one thing
you can do for me.
- Name it.

102
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,596
Think about what
protecting Bernie gets us.

103
00:06:24,788 --> 00:06:27,185
Think about what
offending Caspar loses us.

104
00:06:27,377 --> 00:06:29,487
Oh, come on, Tommy.
You know I don't like to think.

105
00:06:29,679 --> 00:06:31,597
Yeah.

106
00:06:31,789 --> 00:06:35,433
Well, think about
whether you should start.

107
00:08:15,753 --> 00:08:17,863
Wake up, Tommy.

108
00:08:18,055 --> 00:08:20,932
- I am awake.
- Your eyes are shut.

109
00:08:21,028 --> 00:08:23,138
Who you gonna believe?

110
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,798
- How'd I do?
- What do you think?

111
00:08:35,894 --> 00:08:38,483
You are a millionaire.
You gonna remember your friends?

112
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:45,292
- Where's me hat?
- You bet it, mug.

113
00:08:45,388 --> 00:08:48,649
Good thing the game broke up
before you bet your trousers.

114
00:08:49,992 --> 00:08:52,966
- Who made off with me hat?

115
00:08:53,254 --> 00:08:55,843
Verna. Verna and Mink.

116
00:08:55,939 --> 00:08:58,145
- Who?
- Mink and Verna.

117
00:09:05,721 --> 00:09:07,831
Is Thunderclap running tonight?

118
00:09:08,023 --> 00:09:10,996
Thunderclap?
Yeah.

119
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:13,106
What's she leaving at?

120
00:09:13,202 --> 00:09:15,600
Three to one, more than likely.

121
00:09:15,887 --> 00:09:18,861
Lay off, Tom. You shouldn't go
deeper in the hole.

122
00:09:19,052 --> 00:09:21,354
Tell Lazarre...

123
00:09:21,546 --> 00:09:24,711
I want 500 on the nose.

124
00:09:24,903 --> 00:09:27,204
You would have it.

125
00:09:39,768 --> 00:09:42,262
I want me hat.

126
00:09:42,358 --> 00:09:45,906
Is that all you came for?

127
00:09:46,098 --> 00:09:48,304
Yeah. I want me hat.

128
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,414
It's mine. I won it.

129
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:53,004
- What are you gonna do with it?
- Drop dead.

130
00:10:01,252 --> 00:10:03,938
I need a drink.

131
00:10:04,129 --> 00:10:06,527
Why didn't you say so?

132
00:11:00,811 --> 00:11:03,592
Hello, Tommy.
Sorry about the hour.

133
00:11:03,784 --> 00:11:07,333
- I'll live. What's the rumpus?
-Can I come in?

134
00:11:09,922 --> 00:11:12,320
Sure.

135
00:11:20,664 --> 00:11:23,541
- Drink?
- I wouldn't mind.

136
00:11:30,254 --> 00:11:32,172
I tried callin' earlier.

137
00:11:32,364 --> 00:11:34,762
I got home late.

138
00:11:39,941 --> 00:11:44,928
- Well, uh, I'm sorry about the hour.
- Uh-huh.

139
00:11:56,917 --> 00:12:00,274
- Not bad.
- Better than the paint
we sell at the club.

140
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:02,863
That it is. That it is.

141
00:12:06,412 --> 00:12:08,426
- You thought about
cutting Bernie loose?
- Can't do it, Tommy.

142
00:12:08,618 --> 00:12:11,303
Can't do it.

143
00:12:11,495 --> 00:12:13,797
That's sort of why I'm, uh--

144
00:12:16,386 --> 00:12:19,167
Tommy, I don't know where Verna is.

145
00:12:19,455 --> 00:12:22,524
- Uh-huh.
- I know what you're thinkin',
what else is new?

146
00:12:22,716 --> 00:12:25,401
But the situation now--
I'm worried.

147
00:12:25,593 --> 00:12:28,758
Verna can take care of herself,
maybe better than you can.

148
00:12:29,046 --> 00:12:32,307
- What does that mean?
- Want another one?

149
00:12:32,498 --> 00:12:34,225
No.

150
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:36,335
What does that mean?

151
00:12:36,431 --> 00:12:38,636
How far she got
her hooks into you?

152
00:12:38,828 --> 00:12:40,746
That's a hell of a question.

153
00:12:42,952 --> 00:12:44,966
It's a grift.

154
00:12:45,158 --> 00:12:48,515
If she didn't need you
to protect her brother
from Johnny Caspar,

155
00:12:48,707 --> 00:12:52,063
you think she'd still be going
on slow carriage rides with you
through the park?

156
00:12:52,352 --> 00:12:56,380
That's the deal, isn't it?
You keep Bernie under wraps
till Caspar cools down?

157
00:12:56,668 --> 00:13:00,216
Jesus, you're a prickly pear.
What's wrong with her wanting
her brother taken care of?

158
00:13:00,312 --> 00:13:02,134
Nothing. I don't blame her.

159
00:13:02,326 --> 00:13:04,436
She sees the angle,
which is you, she plays it.

160
00:13:04,628 --> 00:13:07,313
She's a grifter,
just like her brother.

161
00:13:07,505 --> 00:13:09,615
Probably had grifter parents
and grifter grandparents...

162
00:13:09,711 --> 00:13:12,588
and someday they're each
gonna spawn little grifter kids.

163
00:13:12,780 --> 00:13:15,753
Stop it, Tommy.
I don't like to hear my friends
run down, even by other friends.

164
00:13:15,945 --> 00:13:17,959
- Friendship's got
nothing to do with it.
- The hell you say.

165
00:13:18,151 --> 00:13:20,740
You'd do anything to help
your friends, like you'd do
anything to kick your enemies.

166
00:13:20,836 --> 00:13:22,275
- Wrong, Leo.
You do things for a reason.
- Okay, Tom.

167
00:13:22,371 --> 00:13:24,193
- Wrong, Leo.
You do things for a reason.
- Okay, Tom.

168
00:13:24,289 --> 00:13:27,166
You know all the angles,
Christ, better than anybody.

169
00:13:29,276 --> 00:13:32,249
But maybe you're wrong
about this. You don't know
what's in Verna's heart.

170
00:13:32,441 --> 00:13:35,030
Leo, if she's such an angel,

171
00:13:35,222 --> 00:13:37,236
why are you looking for her
at 4:00 in the morning?

172
00:13:41,648 --> 00:13:43,374
I put a tail on her this afternoon.

173
00:13:44,813 --> 00:13:49,033
- Uh-huh.
- I asked Rug Daniels
to follow her around,

174
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:52,294
just, you know,
to keep her out of trouble.

175
00:13:52,486 --> 00:13:56,322
I was worried.
After that meeting with Caspar,
you can't be too careful.

176
00:13:56,514 --> 00:13:59,487
- So what did Rug say that has you
scurrying over here?
- That's just it.

177
00:13:59,775 --> 00:14:04,954
- Nothing. He's disappeared.
- So you lost your lady friend
and the tail you put on her?

178
00:14:05,242 --> 00:14:07,639
I guess it does sound
pretty sorry at that.

179
00:14:07,831 --> 00:14:10,996
Help me out, Tom.
I wouldn't know where
to start lookin'.

180
00:14:11,284 --> 00:14:13,586
You know Rug's crowd.
You know the people Verna runs with.

181
00:14:13,777 --> 00:14:17,134
It's just I'm worried now
with things the way they are
between me and Caspar.

182
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:19,915
You shouldn't be confronting
Johnny Caspar. That's what
I've been trying to tell you.

183
00:14:20,011 --> 00:14:22,697
You can't trade
body blows with him.
He's gotten too strong.

184
00:14:22,888 --> 00:14:26,629
I reckon I can still trade body blows
with any man in this town.

185
00:14:30,657 --> 00:14:33,150
Except you, Tom.

186
00:14:33,342 --> 00:14:35,164
And Verna.

187
00:14:44,755 --> 00:14:47,153
Okay. Give me the needle.

188
00:14:49,071 --> 00:14:51,949
I am a sap.

189
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:55,210
I deserve it.

190
00:14:55,498 --> 00:14:57,416
Thanks for the drink.

191
00:14:58,854 --> 00:15:00,964
Let me know
if you hear anything.

192
00:15:28,489 --> 00:15:31,750
- Who was that?
- Leo.

193
00:15:31,942 --> 00:15:33,956
He's lookin' for you.

194
00:15:34,148 --> 00:15:36,450
Did you tell him I was here?

195
00:15:36,546 --> 00:15:38,847
No.

196
00:15:41,341 --> 00:15:44,410
Did you put in a good word
for my brother?

197
00:15:44,698 --> 00:15:46,616
No.

198
00:15:46,807 --> 00:15:49,781
- You said you would.
- I said I'd think about it.

199
00:15:51,892 --> 00:15:53,906
What did you tell him?

200
00:15:56,879 --> 00:15:59,468
Did you see
Rug Daniels last night?

201
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:01,866
No.

202
00:16:01,962 --> 00:16:03,880
What did you tell Leo?

203
00:16:04,072 --> 00:16:06,565
I told him you were a tramp
and he should dump you.

204
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:13,086
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

205
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:25,304
- Hello, Tom.
What's the rumpus?
- Mink.

206
00:17:25,496 --> 00:17:27,414
- I see you got your hat back.
- Yeah, what of it?

207
00:17:27,510 --> 00:17:29,428
Not a thing. Look,
if it ain't my business,
I got not a thing to say.

208
00:17:29,620 --> 00:17:31,442
Listen, Bernie wants to see you.
It's important.

209
00:17:31,538 --> 00:17:33,360
Yeah, well, I'm right here.
I'm not made of glass.

210
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:35,950
He's nervous walkin' around
in public. He's a right guy,
but he's very nervous.

211
00:17:36,142 --> 00:17:38,539
I mean, who wouldn't be?
In the spot he's in,
who wouldn't be?

212
00:17:38,635 --> 00:17:40,841
He asked me to ask you
to ask Leo to take care of him.

213
00:17:40,937 --> 00:17:42,855
Leo listens to you.
Not that Leo wouldn't help
a shmatte anyway.

214
00:17:43,047 --> 00:17:45,157
A guy like Bernie?
A straight shooter like him?

215
00:17:45,349 --> 00:17:47,842
- I don't get it, Mink.
- What's to get? It's as plain
as the nose on your face.

216
00:17:48,034 --> 00:17:50,144
- I thought you were
Eddie Dane's sycophant.
- Yeah, Tom, that's right,

217
00:17:50,336 --> 00:17:52,159
but a guy can have more
than one friend, can't he?

218
00:17:52,255 --> 00:17:55,132
Not that I want the Dane to know
about it, but the shmatte,
he's a right guy, Tommy.

219
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,722
He's got a mixed reputation,
but for a sheeny, he's got
a lot of good qualities.

220
00:17:57,913 --> 00:18:00,886
- What's goin' on
between you and Bernie?
- Nothin', Tom.

221
00:18:01,078 --> 00:18:02,901
We're just...
friends, you know, amigos.

222
00:18:03,092 --> 00:18:05,298
You're a fickle boy, Mink.

223
00:18:05,394 --> 00:18:09,326
If Eddie Dane finds out
that you got another "amigo"--

224
00:18:09,614 --> 00:18:12,971
- Well, I don't peg him
for the understanding type.
- Find out?

225
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:15,656
How's he gonna find out?
Damn it, you and me
ain't even been talkin'!

226
00:18:15,848 --> 00:18:18,150
Jesus, Tom! Damn it!Jesus!

227
