feel like it,

445
00:32:54,076 --> 00:32:55,802
but what the hell is Leo doin'?

446
00:32:55,994 --> 00:33:00,118
Make him listen to you, Tom.
It ain't right, all this fuss
over one sheeny.

447
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:02,995
Let Caspar have Bernie.
What's one Hebrew more or less?

448
00:33:03,187 --> 00:33:05,009
We're burnin'
our meal ticket here.

449
00:33:05,105 --> 00:33:07,215
Leo will do what suits him,
and you'll do what he tells you.

450
00:33:07,311 --> 00:33:09,133
Last I heard, Leo was still
running this town.

451
00:33:09,325 --> 00:33:11,722
Yeah, well, he won't be
for long if this keeps up.

452
00:33:11,914 --> 00:33:14,408
It's no good for anyone.
You said as much yourself.

453
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:18,436
First off, O'Doole, I can
say what I please to Leo
and about him.

454
00:33:18,724 --> 00:33:20,546
You can't.

455
00:33:20,738 --> 00:33:23,998
Second, once Leo decides,
that's that.

456
00:33:24,190 --> 00:33:26,396
If that sticks going down,
there are plenty
of coppers I know...

457
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:29,177
who wouldn't mind
bein' chief and could
swallow it clean.

458
00:33:29,465 --> 00:33:33,205
Jesus, Tom,
I was just speculatin'
about a hypothesis.

459
00:33:33,397 --> 00:33:35,315
I know I don't
know nothin'.

460
00:33:35,411 --> 00:33:37,617
It's just a--
just a damn mess, is all.

461
00:34:01,019 --> 00:34:02,841
Hello, Officer. I'd like to
report an intruder...

462
00:34:02,937 --> 00:34:05,815
at 346 West Lewis--

463
00:34:05,910 --> 00:34:09,267
Who's this?
Hello, Shad. Tom Reagan here.

464
00:34:09,555 --> 00:34:12,048
- You need the booze?
- No, we won't be
needing any today.

465
00:34:12,240 --> 00:34:14,830
- False alarm, huh?
- Yeah. My mother.
She didn't recognize me.

466
00:34:15,022 --> 00:34:17,132
Let me talk to Mulveany.
Miss me?

467
00:34:17,323 --> 00:34:19,529
Drop dead.

468
00:34:19,721 --> 00:34:21,639
- Mulveany here.
- Sean?

469
00:34:21,735 --> 00:34:23,557
Tell O'Doole to get a car
over to Leo's tonight.

470
00:34:23,749 --> 00:34:26,434
If we're banging away
at Caspar, we oughta be ready
for him to bang back.

471
00:34:26,626 --> 00:34:28,640
-
- What do you want?

472
00:34:28,832 --> 00:34:32,285
I was in the neighborhood,
feeling a bit daffy,

473
00:34:32,572 --> 00:34:35,258
so I thought I'd drop in
for an aperitif.

474
00:34:37,080 --> 00:34:39,765
- Rug Daniels is dead.
- Gee, that's tough.

475
00:34:39,957 --> 00:34:41,971
Don't get hysterical.

476
00:34:42,163 --> 00:34:45,424
I've had enough excitement
for one night without a dame
going all weepy on me.

477
00:34:45,616 --> 00:34:47,534
- I barely knew the gentleman.
-Rug?

478
00:34:47,726 --> 00:34:51,755
A bit of a shakedown artist,
not above the occasional grift.

479
00:34:52,042 --> 00:34:55,495
Bet you'd understand that.
All in all, not a bad guy,

480
00:34:55,783 --> 00:34:58,852
if looks, brains
and personality don't count.

481
00:34:59,044 --> 00:35:01,537
- You better hope they don't.
- Yeah, well--

482
00:35:01,633 --> 00:35:04,031
We're none of us the saint
I hear your brother is.

483
00:35:04,222 --> 00:35:06,237
- Who killed him?
- Leo thinks Caspar did.

484
00:35:06,428 --> 00:35:08,251
- But you know better.
- I do now.

485
00:35:08,346 --> 00:35:11,415
You see, Caspar just tried
to buy me into fixing
his tiff with Leo,

486
00:35:11,607 --> 00:35:14,197
which he'd hardly do
if he was waging war.

487
00:35:14,389 --> 00:35:18,129
So I figure you killed him, angel.
You or St. Bernard.

488
00:35:18,225 --> 00:35:21,773
Why would I or my brother
kill Rug Daniels or anybody else?

489
00:35:21,965 --> 00:35:25,706
Rug was following you.
He knew about you and me,

490
00:35:25,993 --> 00:35:28,391
and that wouldn't help
your play with Leo, would it?

491
00:35:28,583 --> 00:35:30,501
You think I murdered someone?

492
00:35:30,693 --> 00:35:33,474
Come on, Tom.
You know me a little.

493
00:35:33,666 --> 00:35:35,967
Nobody knows anybody.
Not that well.

494
00:35:36,159 --> 00:35:38,173
You know, or you
wouldn't be here.

495
00:35:38,365 --> 00:35:41,434
Not at all, sugar.
I came to hear your side of the story.

496
00:35:41,626 --> 00:35:45,846
How horrible Rug was,
how he goaded you into it,
how he tried to shake you down.

497
00:35:46,134 --> 00:35:48,052
- That's not why
you came either.
- Tell me why I came.

498
00:35:48,243 --> 00:35:51,122
- The oldest reason there is.
- There are friendlier
places to drink.

499
00:35:51,313 --> 00:35:53,136
- Why can't you admit it?
- Admit what?

500
00:35:53,232 --> 00:35:56,301
That you don't like
me seeing Leo
'cause you're jealous.

501
00:35:56,492 --> 00:35:58,602
Admit that you've
got a heart,

502
00:35:58,794 --> 00:36:01,096
even though it may be
small and feeble...

503
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:03,206
and you can't remember
the last time you used it.

504
00:36:03,398 --> 00:36:06,275
If I'd known we were gonna
cast our feelings into words,

505
00:36:06,467 --> 00:36:08,864
I'd have memorized
the Song of Solomon.

506
00:36:10,974 --> 00:36:13,947
Maybe that's why
I like you, Tom.

507
00:36:14,043 --> 00:36:16,633
I never knew anybody
that made being
a son of a bitch...

508
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:19,414
such a point of pride.

509
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:22,291
Though one day you'll
pay the price for it.

510
00:36:23,730 --> 00:36:27,278
Okay, Verna.
But until then, let's get stinko.

511
00:36:27,470 --> 00:36:29,772
Let's do something else first.

512
00:36:34,471 --> 00:36:36,677
Yeah. Let's do plenty.

513
00:40:24,745 --> 00:40:27,335
- Who's winning?
- We are, for the nonce.

514
00:40:27,431 --> 00:40:31,267
- What's the "disposish"?
- Last night, four to one. Dana
Cudahy went up with the house.

515
00:40:31,555 --> 00:40:33,569
- And theirs?
- One burned.

516
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:35,391
- The other three?
- Lead.

517
00:40:35,487 --> 00:40:37,405
- Whose?
- Leo's.

518
00:40:37,501 --> 00:40:39,611
The old man's still
an artist with a Thompson.

519
00:40:39,803 --> 00:40:41,625
Yeah, do that.

520
00:40:41,625 --> 00:40:45,269
Well, find him, goddamn it!
Go and see if he fell in the john.

521
00:40:46,900 --> 00:40:49,585
Son of a bitch. No chief.

522
00:40:49,778 --> 00:40:52,847
- Who's mindin' the goddamn store?
-Can't raise O'Doole?

523
00:40:53,039 --> 00:40:54,957
No, nor the mayor either.

524
00:40:55,149 --> 00:40:59,177
- That's not good.
They're running.
- They wouldn't dare!

525
00:40:59,368 --> 00:41:01,862
I don't know, Leo.
I warned you not to
hit Caspar's club.

526
00:41:02,054 --> 00:41:04,643
- I'm still here, ain't I?
-Caspar's play hurt you anyway.

527
00:41:04,739 --> 00:41:07,041
That sorry son of a bitch
just slit his own throat.

528
00:41:07,233 --> 00:41:10,110
Listen to me, Leo.
Last night made you
look vulnerable.

529
00:41:10,398 --> 00:41:13,563
You don't hold elected office
in this town. You run it
because people think you run it.

530
00:41:13,658 --> 00:41:16,248
Once they stop thinking it,
you stop running it.

531
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:19,509
Jesus, Tom. It sounds like
a bad break for me
I wasn't killed!

532
00:41:19,796 --> 00:41:22,578
I mean it, Leo.
Start taking Caspar seriously.

533
00:41:22,770 --> 00:41:26,702
I know, I know.
Retreat to win, give up Bernie.
That'll solve all our problems.

534
00:41:26,894 --> 00:41:28,812
Won't anymore, I'll grant you that.

535
00:41:29,003 --> 00:41:31,305
But going toe-to-toe
with a psychopath
will get you nowhere.

536
00:41:31,401 --> 00:41:33,895
It'll force people
to choose sides just when
you're looking shaky.

537
00:41:34,087 --> 00:41:37,060
- The hell I do!
- Then where's the mayor?

538
00:41:37,251 --> 00:41:39,361
Why aren't there
any police here?

539
00:41:39,457 --> 00:41:41,375
Why weren't there any police
at your place last night?

540
00:41:41,471 --> 00:41:43,869
- I didn't ask for any.
- I did.

541
00:41:47,034 --> 00:41:49,624
Mother hen, huh?
What's the matter, Tommy?

542
00:41:49,816 --> 00:41:53,077
- Don't you think
I can take care of myself?
- I know you can't.

543
00:41:53,269 --> 00:41:55,858
Here's the smart play, Leo.
You lay back, you give Bernie up,

544
00:41:56,050 --> 00:41:57,872
you let Caspar think
he's made his point.

545
00:41:58,064 --> 00:42:00,749
- Then you wait for him
to show a weakness.
- Please, Tom.

546
00:42:01,037 --> 00:42:03,051
You're sticking on Bernie.
You're sticking your neck out...

547
00:42:03,243 --> 00:42:05,928
for a guy who'd chop you off
at the heels if there
was two bits in it.

548
00:42:08,422 --> 00:42:10,916
Tom,

549
00:42:11,107 --> 00:42:14,176
things aren't as, uh,
clear-cut as you make it.

550
00:42:15,807 --> 00:42:19,643
Bernie's--
Well, hell,you know
about me and Verna.

551
00:42:19,835 --> 00:42:23,383
Things now are, uh--

552
00:42:23,575 --> 00:42:27,028
Not that I haven't
been a gentleman, but--

553
00:42:29,234 --> 00:42:32,399
I plan to ask her
to marry me, Tom.

554
00:42:37,002 --> 00:42:40,167
I guess you think
that's a bonehead play.

555
00:42:44,387 --> 00:42:47,839
- You think she wants you to?
- How the hell do I know?

556
00:42:48,127 --> 00:42:50,622
I think she does.
Yeah, of course she does.

557
00:42:50,814 --> 00:42:54,362
I know you think different,
but, well, we just, uh--

558
00:42:54,554 --> 00:42:56,760
We just differ on that.

559
00:42:59,541 --> 00:43:02,418
Leo, Caspar didn't kill Rug.

560
00:43:02,610 --> 00:43:06,063
- Course he did.
- No. Think about it
just this one time.

561
00:43:06,350 --> 00:43:08,173
- Who was Rug following?
- Huh?

562
00:43:08,364 --> 00:43:11,625
It needn't have been that
sinister. Strange man follows
her down a dark alleyway.

563
00:43:11,817 --> 00:43:14,023
- I told you she can
look after herself.
- Verna wouldn't panic,

564
00:43:14,119 --> 00:43:17,092
shoot someone just because
he was following her.

565
00:43:17,284 --> 00:43:20,736
Nah, it wouldn't have happened
like that, and if it had
she would have told me.

566
00:43:21,024 --> 00:43:23,997
They pulled a .22 slug out of him.
A pop gun, Leo, a woman's gun.

567
00:43:24,189 --> 00:43:26,203
I know you don't
like her, Tom,

568
00:43:26,299 --> 00:43:29,080
but I trust Verna
as much as I trust you.

569
00:43:30,711 --> 00:43:32,533
Okay, Leo.

570
00:43:32,629 --> 00:43:34,739
Maybe it wasn't that innocent.

571
00:43:34,930 --> 00:43:38,287
Maybe Rug knew something
she didn't like him knowing
and wouldn't want you to know.

572
00:43:38,575 --> 00:43:41,932
Rug was following her.
Maybe he knew
where she was sleeping,

573
00:43:42,123 --> 00:43:43,850
and who with.

574
00:43:47,878 --> 00:43:50,181
Maybes don't make it so.

575
00:43:51,331 --> 00:43:53,154
There's more than maybes.

576
00:43:53,345 --> 00:43:56,606
You've trusted me before,
you've never lost anything
by it. Trust me on this.

577
00:43:59,483 --> 00:44:02,648
- This is too important.
- I don't ask much,
and I don't ask often.

578
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:05,046
Trust me on this.

579
00:44:05,238 --> 00:44:08,211
- Tommy.
- Trust me on this,
or to hell with you.

580
00:44:10,896 --> 00:44:13,006
You don't mean that.

581
00:44:15,883 --> 00:44:17,610
She was with me...

582
00:44:17,706 --> 00:44:20,871
the night Rug
was following her,

583
00:44:21,062 --> 00:44:22,885
the night you dropped by.

584
00:44:36,024 --> 00:44:38,230
Oh.

585
00:46:29,675 --> 00:46:32,264
Okay, Leo. Okay.
I'll throw him out.

586
00:46:34,374 --> 00:46:36,772
Yeah, do that.

587
00:46:37,923 --> 00:46:39,937
It's the kiss-off.

588
00:46:40,128 --> 00:46:43,197
If I never see him again,
it'll be soon enough.

589
00:46:53,173 --> 00:46:55,091
- Hello?
- Hello, Frankie.

590
00:46:55,187 --> 00:46:57,489
It's Tom.
How's the flunky business?

591
00:46:58,831 --> 00:47:00,941
I've had worse.
Your ventilator mending?

592
00:47:01,133 --> 00:47:04,010
-
- Tell Caspar it's forgotten.

593
00:47:04,202 --> 00:47:06,408
- I'd like to see him.

594
00:47:08,134 --> 00:47:10,148
Ah. All right, let me know.

595
00:47:53,690 --> 00:47:57,334
It worked, whatever you did.

596
00:47:57,622 --> 00:48:00,691
Leo says we're quits.

597
00:48:00,883 --> 00:48:03,376
But you know I didn't have
anything to do with Rug.

598
00:48:03,472 --> 00:48:06,062
Maybe not.

599
00:48:06,253 --> 00:48:08,076
Anyway, that isn't
what soured him on you.

600
00:48:08,267 --> 00:48:10,377
Oh, you and me, huh?

601
00:48:12,104 --> 00:48:15,460
You always take
the long way around to get
what you want, don't you, Tom?

602
00:48:17,666 --> 00:48:19,872
You could have just asked.

603
00:48:22,749 --> 00:48:25,435
What did I want?

604
00:48:25,626 --> 00:48:28,024
Me.

605
00:48:53,057 --> 00:48:55,646
Yeah?

606
00:48:55,742 --> 00:48:57,564
Yeah, yeah.

607
00:48:57,756 --> 00:48:59,866
When?

608
00:49:00,058 --> 00:49:01,784
Okay.

609
00:49:06,579 --> 00:49:09,073
You still up?

610
00:49:09,265 --> 00:49:11,279
Yeah.

611
00:49:15,019 --> 00:49:17,800
What are you chewin' over?

612
00:49:18,088 --> 00:49:20,102
Dream I had once.

613
00:49:22,020 --> 00:49:24,706
I was walking in the woods.
I don't know why.

614
00:49:26,336 --> 00:49:29,213
Wind came whippin'.
Blew me hat off.

615
00:49:31,227 --> 00:49:33,913
And you chased it, right?

616
00:49:34,104 --> 00:49:36,310
You ran and ran.

617
00:49:36,502 --> 00:49:39,379
You finally caught up to it.

618
00:49:39,667 --> 00:49:43,407
And you picked it up,
but it wasn't a hat anymore.

619
00:49:43,695 --> 00:49:47,340
It had changed into something else,
something wonderful.

620
00:49:47,435 --> 00:49:50,122
No, it stayed a hat.

621
00:49:50,218 --> 00:49:52,519
And no, I didn't chase it.

622
00:49:53,958 --> 00:49:57,507
Nothing more foolish
than a man chasin' his hat.

623
00:49:57,794 --> 00:49:59,808
Where are you going?

624
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:02,494
Just have to do a few things.

625
00:50:02,686 --> 00:50:05,850
- You and Leo might still
be able to patch things up.
- Me and Leo are finished.

626
00:50:06,042 --> 00:50:09,207
-Nothing's gonna change that.
- You never know.

627
00:50:09,495 --> 00:50:12,948
- He's got a big heart.
- We're quits as far as I'm
concerned, never mind him.

628
00:50:13,139 --> 00:50:17,071
And if Leo did want me back,
he's an even bigger sap
than I thought.

629
00:50:17,359 --> 00:50:19,661
Then why don't we just
pick up and leave town?

630
00:50:19,757 --> 00:50:22,442
There's nothing keeping you here.

631
00:50:22,538 --> 00:50:24,360
I know there's nothing keeping me.

632
00:50:24,552 --> 00:50:27,621
- What about Bernie?
- He could go with us.

633
00:50:28,964 --> 00:50:30,882
You, me and Bernie?
Where would we go, Verna?

634
00:50:31,074 --> 00:50:32,896
Niagara Falls?

635
00:50:32,992 --> 00:50:34,814
Why do you hate him?

636
00:50:34,910 --> 00:50:36,732
- I don't hate anyone.
-Or like anyone.

637
00:50:41,623 --> 00:50:43,638
Where is Bernie?

638
00:50:43,733 --> 00:50:46,035
- Why?
- Leo can't protect him anymore.

639
00:50:46,227 --> 00:50:49,393
I oughta tell him to skip.

640
00:50:49,681 --> 00:50:51,407
The Royale, room 302.

641
00:50:56,586 --> 00:50:59,943
I guess we both
double-crossed Leo, huh?

642
00:51:00,134 --> 00:51:01,861
There's no gettin' around that.

643
00:51:03,107 --> 00:51:05,697
I guess he's well rid
of both of us.

644
00:51:05,889 --> 00:51:09,917
The two of us, we're about
bad enough to deserve each other.

645
00:51:13,369 --> 00:51:15,192
Are we?

646
00:51:17,302 --> 00:51:19,987
We're a couple of heels, Tom.

647
00:51:20,083 --> 00:51:22,576
Yes, we are.

648
00:51:22,864 --> 00:51:26,892
So he says,
"Screw him. Give him a dollar.
This was my idea. "

649
00:51:27,180 --> 00:51:30,537
Hello, Tom.

650
00:51:30,824 --> 00:51:33,798
Uh, you know O'Doole
and the mayor.

651
00:51:33,989 --> 00:51:36,962
- Hello, boys.
- Tom's a big booster.
Always has been.

652
00:51:37,154 --> 00:51:40,895
That's fine, that's fine.
Well, Tom and I got
the proverbial fat to chew.

653
00:51:41,182 --> 00:51:43,772
-Just let us know
if you need anything.
- Yeah. Happy days.

654
00:51:43,964 --> 00:51:46,745
Have a seat, kid.
Yeah, that's it.

655
00:51:47,033 --> 00:51:50,103
So,you had enough time
to think about things?

656
00:51:50,198 --> 00:51:54,035
- Yeah, well, uh,
circumstances have changed.
- Don't I know it.

657
00:51:54,227 --> 00:51:57,104
Last night I know the Dane
was disappointed
the bulls showed up...

658
00:51:57,296 --> 00:51:59,693
before Frankie and Tic-Tac
really pinned your ears back,

659
00:51:59,885 --> 00:52:04,009
but I said, "Relax, Eddie.
I got a feeling about this kid.

660
00:52:04,297 --> 00:52:08,133
The kid and Leo
are gonna go bust-o.
Matter of time."

661
00:52:08,421 --> 00:52:10,914
I said, "The kid
is too smart for Leo."
That's what I said.

662
00:52:11,010 --> 00:52:13,887
Like a psychic.
Ask the Dane if I did.
Like a goddamn psychic.

663
00:52:13,983 --> 00:52:16,285
-Go ahead, ask him.
- You vouch for that
psychic business?

664
00:52:16,477 --> 00:52:18,874
- That's right, smart guy.
-I know you knew...

665
00:52:18,970 --> 00:52:21,752
protecting the shmatte
was a dumb idea.

666
00:52:22,039 --> 00:52:25,492
I know you've been wise
to all of Leo's dumb ideas lately.

667
00:52:25,588 --> 00:52:27,602
Only a matter of time-- bust-o.

668
00:52:27,698 --> 00:52:30,671
That's why last night
we didn't put the arm on you,
only Leo.

669
00:52:30,767 --> 00:52:34,028
Seeing how you squiffed
your play on Leo,
I can only be so grateful.

670
00:52:34,315 --> 00:52:38,248
- Oh, that's real brave coming
from Little Miss Punching Bag.
- Okay, Eddie.

671
00:52:38,535 --> 00:52:41,508
- Friends now, huh?
- Nuts.

