897
01:07:07,748 --> 01:07:11,105
You know what,yegg?
I believe you.

898
01:07:32,396 --> 01:07:34,314
Go ahead and run, sweetie.

899
01:07:34,506 --> 01:07:37,671
I'll track down
all of you whores.

900
01:08:35,598 --> 01:08:39,051
Hello, Bernie. Come on in.
Make yourself at home.

901
01:08:39,242 --> 01:08:42,024
Hello, Tom.

902
01:08:42,216 --> 01:08:45,668
I thought I'd do that,
since you didn't seem to be in.

903
01:08:45,956 --> 01:08:49,793
Figured it was a bad idea
to wait in the hall, seeing
as I'm supposed to be dead.

904
01:08:52,862 --> 01:08:55,164
How'd you know it was me?

905
01:08:55,260 --> 01:08:57,562
You're the only one I know
who'd knock and then break in.

906
01:08:57,753 --> 01:08:59,576
Your other friends
wouldn't break in?

907
01:08:59,767 --> 01:09:02,645
My other friends
want to kill me,
so they wouldn't knock.

908
01:09:02,836 --> 01:09:05,138
What's on your mind. Bernie?

909
01:09:07,536 --> 01:09:09,742
Things.

910
01:09:09,838 --> 01:09:14,921
I guess you must be angry.
I'm supposed to be
gone far away.

911
01:09:15,112 --> 01:09:17,990
I guess it seems sort of
irresponsible, my being here.

912
01:09:20,579 --> 01:09:23,840
And I was gonna leave.
Honest, I was.

913
01:09:23,936 --> 01:09:25,758
But then I started thinking...

914
01:09:25,950 --> 01:09:28,539
if I stuck around,
that would not be good for you.

915
01:09:28,731 --> 01:09:31,225
Then I started
thinking that--

916
01:09:31,416 --> 01:09:33,622
that might not
be bad for me.

917
01:09:36,883 --> 01:09:39,377
You didn't see
the play you gave me.

918
01:09:39,569 --> 01:09:41,678
I mean, what am I gonna do?

919
01:09:41,774 --> 01:09:44,460
If I leave, I got nothing.

920
01:09:44,652 --> 01:09:47,146
No money, no friends, nothing.

921
01:09:47,338 --> 01:09:49,352
If I stay, I got you.

922
01:09:49,448 --> 01:09:53,668
Anyone finds out I'm alive,
you're dead, so...

923
01:09:55,874 --> 01:09:57,792
I got-- I got you, Tommy.

924
01:10:00,285 --> 01:10:03,450
What's the matter?
You got nothing
to crack wise about?

925
01:10:03,546 --> 01:10:05,848
Bernie ain't
so funny anymore?

926
01:10:09,013 --> 01:10:11,698
I guess I made kind of
a fool of myself out there...

927
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:16,302
bawling away like a twist.

928
01:10:16,493 --> 01:10:18,699
I guess--

929
01:10:18,891 --> 01:10:20,617
I guess I turned yellow.

930
01:10:20,809 --> 01:10:24,262
- You didn't tell anyone
about that?
- No.

931
01:10:24,358 --> 01:10:26,372
Of course,
you know about it.

932
01:10:30,304 --> 01:10:32,318
It's a painful memory...

933
01:10:34,140 --> 01:10:38,648
and I can't help remembering
that you put the finger on me,

934
01:10:38,840 --> 01:10:41,717
and you took me out there
to whack me.

935
01:10:42,005 --> 01:10:45,265
I know... you didn't.
I know.

936
01:10:45,457 --> 01:10:49,007
- You didn't shoot me, but--
- But what have I done
for you lately?

937
01:10:49,198 --> 01:10:51,117
Don't smart me.

938
01:10:52,651 --> 01:10:54,857
See, I want
to watch you squirm.

939
01:10:56,487 --> 01:10:58,789
I want to see you
sweat a little.

940
01:11:00,707 --> 01:11:02,625
And when you smart me...

941
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:06,366
it ruins it.

942
01:11:15,860 --> 01:11:18,162
There's one other thing I want.

943
01:11:20,080 --> 01:11:22,670
I want to seeJohnny Caspar
cold and stiff.

944
01:11:22,766 --> 01:11:25,931
That's what you'll do
for your friend Bernie.

945
01:11:29,095 --> 01:11:32,069
In the meantime,
I'll stay out of sight.

946
01:11:32,260 --> 01:11:35,425
But if Caspar ain't stiff
in a couple of days...

947
01:11:35,617 --> 01:11:37,535
I start eating
in restaurants.

948
01:11:50,963 --> 01:11:52,977
Oof!.

949
01:11:56,813 --> 01:11:59,403
Uuh!

950
01:11:59,595 --> 01:12:01,513
You make me laugh, Tommy.

951
01:12:01,609 --> 01:12:04,965
You're gonna catch cold.
Then you're no good to me.

952
01:12:05,061 --> 01:12:07,747
What were you gonna do
if you caught me?

953
01:12:08,034 --> 01:12:11,199
I'd just squirt a few,
and then you'd let me go again.

954
01:12:18,009 --> 01:12:21,078
Hello, Tad.
How's the club holding up?

955
01:12:21,270 --> 01:12:24,626
We're managing to squeak by
without you.
Got Lazarre's money?

956
01:12:24,914 --> 01:12:27,791
- No.
- You're not supposed to be here
since you turned rat.

957
01:12:27,887 --> 01:12:30,285
Relax, Tad.
Leo isn't around, is he?

958
01:12:30,477 --> 01:12:34,217
Last couple of days you booked
any heavy bets on a long shot
at Saturday's fights?

959
01:12:34,505 --> 01:12:36,423
Why the hell
should I tell you?

960
01:12:36,519 --> 01:12:40,067
The truth is, Tad,
no reason on Earth.

961
01:12:42,753 --> 01:12:44,575
Saturday's fights?

962
01:12:44,671 --> 01:12:48,316
DropJohnson put two grand
on one yesterday--

963
01:12:48,604 --> 01:12:51,769
on Sailor Reese,
an undercard bum.

964
01:12:51,865 --> 01:12:54,742
DropJohnson.
He play your book much?

965
01:12:54,934 --> 01:12:58,003
- Are you kidding? I didn't
even know he could count.

966
01:12:58,194 --> 01:13:00,208
Jesus. You bring them with you?

967
01:13:00,400 --> 01:13:03,565
Hello, Brian.
Still fighting the good fight?

968
01:13:03,757 --> 01:13:05,867
Hello, Tom.
Neither rain nor wind nor snow.

969
01:13:06,059 --> 01:13:07,977
That's the mailman. O'Doole here?

970
01:13:14,211 --> 01:13:16,896
Hello, O'Doole.
You don't look happy.

971
01:13:17,088 --> 01:13:19,006
Look at this mess.

972
01:13:19,198 --> 01:13:22,267
Guttin' the golden calf again.
I don't know whether to laugh or cry.

973
01:13:22,459 --> 01:13:25,911
Yeah, it's awful confusing.
You know a yegg
named DropJohnson?

974
01:13:26,103 --> 01:13:28,597
- We spanked him
a couple of times.
- Where does he flop?

975
01:13:28,789 --> 01:13:30,803
- Terminal Hotel, Bay Street.

976
01:13:30,994 --> 01:13:35,022
Jesus!
Look, don't nobody ask me since
I'm just the chief around here,

977
01:13:35,310 --> 01:13:37,228
but I'll tell you my opinion.

978
01:13:37,420 --> 01:13:41,352
Caspar is just as crazy as Leo,
and an "eye-tie"
into the bargain.

979
01:13:41,640 --> 01:13:44,517
What's the matter, O'Doole?
Doesn't anything ever suit you?

980
01:13:54,301 --> 01:13:56,890
Hop in, Tom.
We been lookin'for you.

981
01:13:57,178 --> 01:13:59,384
- I'm busy.
- Hop in anyway.

982
01:13:59,575 --> 01:14:02,549
You can't hijack me, Tic-Tac.
We're on the same side now.

983
01:14:02,740 --> 01:14:05,330
Or didn't you get
that far in school?

984
01:14:14,345 --> 01:14:16,071
How'd you get the fat lip?

985
01:14:16,263 --> 01:14:20,291
- Old war wound.
Acts up around morons.
- Very smart.

986
01:14:20,483 --> 01:14:23,360
What were you doing
at the club, talking
things over with Leo?

987
01:14:23,552 --> 01:14:26,237
Don't think so hard, Eddie.
You might sprain something.

988
01:14:26,429 --> 01:14:28,923
You are so goddamn smart.

989
01:14:29,115 --> 01:14:30,841
Except you ain't.

990
01:14:31,033 --> 01:14:33,718
I get you, smart guy.
I know what you are.

991
01:14:33,910 --> 01:14:35,732
Straight as a corkscrew.

992
01:14:35,828 --> 01:14:37,650
Mr. Inside Out-ski,

993
01:14:37,746 --> 01:14:41,582
like some goddamn Bolshevik
picking up his orders
from Yegg Central.

994
01:14:41,870 --> 01:14:43,788
You think you're
so goddamn smart.

995
01:14:43,980 --> 01:14:45,994
You join upJohnny Caspar,

996
01:14:46,090 --> 01:14:48,009
you bump Bernie Bernbaum.

997
01:14:49,256 --> 01:14:52,421
Up is down. Black is white.

998
01:14:53,763 --> 01:14:56,641
Well, I think you're half smart.

999
01:14:56,737 --> 01:14:59,134
I think you were straight
with your frail,

1000
01:14:59,326 --> 01:15:01,724
I think you were queer
with Johnny Caspar...

1001
01:15:01,916 --> 01:15:05,752
and I think you'd sooner
join a ladies' league
than gun a guy down.

1002
01:15:06,040 --> 01:15:10,068
Then I hear from these
two geniuses they never even
saw this rub-out take place.

1003
01:15:10,355 --> 01:15:13,808
- Boss said to have him do it.
He didn't say nothing about--
- Shut up!

1004
01:15:14,096 --> 01:15:17,069
Or maybe you still got
too many teeth.

1005
01:15:19,658 --> 01:15:23,494
Everyone is so goddamn smart.

1006
01:15:23,782 --> 01:15:27,235
Well, we'll go out
to Miller's Crossing...

1007
01:15:27,331 --> 01:15:30,112
and we'll see who's smart.

1008
01:15:53,418 --> 01:15:57,350
You understand if we don't
find a stiff out here,
we leave a fresh one.

1009
01:16:13,750 --> 01:16:16,436
Where are your friends
when you need 'em, huh?

1010
01:16:17,778 --> 01:16:19,984
Where's Leo now?

1011
01:16:21,998 --> 01:16:24,204
Hey, Tic-Tac!

1012
01:16:24,396 --> 01:16:27,944
You ever notice how
the snappy dialogue dries up...

1013
01:16:28,040 --> 01:16:30,438
once a guy starts
soiling his union suit?

1014
01:17:12,638 --> 01:17:16,570
Okay. There's nothing out here.

1015
01:17:29,230 --> 01:17:33,641
- Think about this... smart guy.

1016
01:17:33,833 --> 01:17:36,518
It's hanky time.

1017
01:17:41,218 --> 01:17:44,287
- Birds have been at him.

1018
01:17:44,479 --> 01:17:46,781
Jesus Christ.

1019
01:18:10,566 --> 01:18:14,211
Told you
to put one in his brain,
not in his stinkin' face!

1020
01:18:18,143 --> 01:18:21,595
I told you, Dane.
We heard two shots.

1021
01:18:48,162 --> 01:18:50,081
Hello, Drop.

1022
01:18:53,725 --> 01:18:55,931
How are the Katzenjammers?

1023
01:18:56,123 --> 01:18:58,616
Hello, Tom. What's the rumpus?

1024
01:19:00,055 --> 01:19:02,068
Had any visitors?

1025
01:19:02,260 --> 01:19:04,178
Uhh, no.

1026
01:19:04,370 --> 01:19:06,096
Not ever, Drop?

1027
01:19:06,192 --> 01:19:08,014
Not lately.

1028
01:19:08,206 --> 01:19:10,508
Then you must be happy to see me.

1029
01:19:13,768 --> 01:19:15,495
So, uh...

1030
01:19:15,687 --> 01:19:19,235
you didn't see Bernie Bernbaum
before he was shown across.

1031
01:19:19,427 --> 01:19:21,249
Uh, no.

1032
01:19:21,441 --> 01:19:23,263
Seen him since?

1033
01:19:25,469 --> 01:19:27,579
One last question, Drop.

1034
01:19:27,771 --> 01:19:31,991
You got a lot of money
on tomorrow's fight.

1035
01:19:32,278 --> 01:19:36,019
That your bet, or, uh...
you placing it for a friend?

1036
01:19:36,210 --> 01:19:38,033
No, no, no, it's my bet.

1037
01:19:38,129 --> 01:19:42,444
- I just have a good feeling
about that fight.
- A good feeling, huh?

1038
01:19:42,732 --> 01:19:45,130
When did a feeling
return to your head?

1039
01:19:45,322 --> 01:19:47,720
You've outgrown that one.

1040
01:19:47,912 --> 01:19:49,926
Must be all the thinking
you been doing.

1041
01:19:50,118 --> 01:19:52,899
Tell Bernie something's come up,
he has to get in touch.

1042
01:19:53,187 --> 01:19:55,968
There'll be nothing stirring
till I talk to him.

1043
01:20:27,042 --> 01:20:31,837
All right, anyone left in there,
come on out grabbing air.
You know the drill.

1044
01:20:47,279 --> 01:20:49,773
Aah!

1045
01:21:30,916 --> 01:21:33,602
Hello, Tom.
Where you been hiding?

1046
01:21:33,794 --> 01:21:35,904
Hither and yon.
Is the mayor in?

1047
01:21:35,999 --> 01:21:38,301
- He's with Mr. Caspar.
- That's who I'm looking for.

1048
01:21:38,493 --> 01:21:41,466
- Scare me up some gargle, will you?
- Sure. I'll announce you.

1049
01:21:41,562 --> 01:21:44,151
Don't bother. I'm well-liked.

1050
01:21:45,878 --> 01:21:48,756
I can't do it.
I'll look ridiculous.
It simply isn't done.

1051
01:21:48,948 --> 01:21:51,729
-Assistants, maybe.
- For a mayor, you don't hear so hot.

1052
01:21:51,921 --> 01:21:54,702
I said head.
Head of the assessor's office.

1053
01:21:54,894 --> 01:21:58,730
- But there are two of them.
- I can count. Co-heads.

1054
01:21:59,018 --> 01:22:01,799
Johnny, needless to say,
this office will do
anything in its power...

1055
01:22:01,991 --> 01:22:04,389
to assist you and your cousins.

1056
01:22:04,581 --> 01:22:06,019
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1057
01:22:06,115 --> 01:22:08,033
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1058
01:22:08,129 --> 01:22:11,773
Damn right.
Had every potato-eater from
County Cork on the public tit.

1059
01:22:11,965 --> 01:22:14,171
But there's a way we do things,

1060
01:22:14,363 --> 01:22:17,240
hallowed by usage
and consecrated by time.

1061
01:22:17,528 --> 01:22:22,227
- When we put people on the pad
when Leo was running things--
- Leo ain't runnin' things!

1062
01:22:22,419 --> 01:22:26,543
I ain't interested
in ancient history!
I'm runnin'things now!

1063
01:22:26,735 --> 01:22:29,037
Nobody can appreciate it
more than I.

1064
01:22:29,228 --> 01:22:31,338
I can give them jobs.
I can give them good jobs.

1065
01:22:31,530 --> 01:22:34,407
I can even give them jobs
where they won't have
to perform any work,

1066
01:22:34,599 --> 01:22:37,189
where their lack of English
will be no impediment, but I can't--

1067
01:22:37,285 --> 01:22:39,394
What is this, the high hat?

1068
01:22:39,586 --> 01:22:44,382
Tom, can you explain it to him?
I can put them in public works,
but I can't--

1069
01:22:44,669 --> 01:22:46,397
You can do whatever
the hell Caspar tells you.

1070
01:22:46,588 --> 01:22:48,890
I don't remember
all this double talk
when Leo gave you an order.

1071
01:22:48,986 --> 01:22:52,918
- Tom.Jesus!
- Stop whimpering
and do as you're told.

1072
01:22:53,206 --> 01:22:56,179
- You can start
by gettin'out of here.
-Johnny, it's my office.

1073
01:22:56,275 --> 01:23:00,879
Get out of here!
Take it on the heel and toe
before I whack you one!

1074
01:23:03,276 --> 01:23:05,482
- You two beat it.

1075
01:23:05,578 --> 01:23:09,414
-
- Yeah, go and keep
the mayor company.

1076
01:23:09,702 --> 01:23:12,483
I'll take care
of ya's later.

1077
01:23:21,690 --> 01:23:24,376
- Runnin' things--
it ain't all gravy.

1078
01:23:24,663 --> 01:23:28,404
- What's the fireworks?
-Knocking over one of Leo's clubs.

1079
01:23:28,595 --> 01:23:31,473
Son of a bitch
won't go belly up.

1080
01:23:31,760 --> 01:23:34,638
I'm sorry, kid.
I heard about your
little ride this morning.

1081
01:23:34,829 --> 01:23:36,556
Yeah, well,
sorry don't fix things.

1082
01:23:36,747 --> 01:23:40,296
We could just as easily
have missed Bernie's corpse,
and I'd be dead now.

1083
01:23:40,392 --> 01:23:43,845
I know, I know, but that don't mean
the Dane's up to anything.

1084
01:23:44,132 --> 01:23:47,682
So he hears a rumor
that Bernie ain't dead.
These stories pop up.

1085
01:23:47,874 --> 01:23:50,847
Any stories
about Bernie being alive
the Dane's made up himself.

1086
01:23:51,038 --> 01:23:54,587
You don't know that.
It don't make sense. Why would he?

1087
01:23:54,875 --> 01:23:57,081
There could be
a damn good reason...

1088
01:23:58,807 --> 01:24:01,396
if you got
a fixed fight coming up.

1089
01:24:03,698 --> 01:24:06,575
- Do you?
- Maybe.

1090
01:24:08,302 --> 01:24:12,042
Okay, yeah, sure.
Tomorrow night.
The fix is in. What of it?

1091
01:24:12,234 --> 01:24:14,344
- The Dane know about it?
- Yeah.

1092
01:24:18,084 --> 01:24:20,482
Okay, I get it.

1093
01:24:20,674 --> 01:24:23,359
If the Dane's been selling
you out on these fights
and means to again,

1094
01:24:23,551 --> 01:24:26,428
- he's gonna have to have somebody
else to point the finger at.
- Yeah, I get it.

1095
01:24:26,620 --> 01:24:28,826
With Bernie dead,
there ain't a hell of a lot
of people he can point to.

1096
01:24:29,017 --> 01:24:32,470
Yeah, the Dane sells me out,
makes pretend Bernie's still
doing it.

1097
01:24:32,662 --> 01:24:34,484
That's real pretty.

1098
01:24:34,676 --> 01:24:38,416
Bernie leaked the fix,
and you take the fall
for not killing him.

1099
01:24:40,526 --> 01:24:44,650
But I don't know.
Why would Eddie cross me
like that? Money?

1100
01:24:44,842 --> 01:24:46,953
Okay, everybody likes money,

1101
01:24:47,049 --> 01:24:50,022
but somehow it just
don't seem like him.

1102
01:24:50,214 --> 01:24:54,338
- And I know the Dane.
- Nobody knows anybody.
Not that well.

1103
01:24:54,625 --> 01:24:57,119
Money don't mean
that much to him.

1104
01:24:57,311 --> 01:24:59,325
Then it's not just
the money he's after.

1105
01:24:59,517 --> 01:25:02,969
- He's got a wart on his fanny.
- Huh?

1106
01:25:03,161 --> 01:25:06,518
A wart on his fanny
giving him the fidgets.

1107
01:25:06,614 --> 01:25:08,915
Maybe he's sick of sitting
on the couch.

1108
01:25:09,107 --> 01:25:12,080
Maybe behind your desk
don't look like a bad place to move to.

1109
01:25:12,176 --> 01:25:14,478
Kid, you got a lip on you.

1110
01:25:15,725 --> 01:25:17,931
But you're honest.

1111
01:25:18,122 --> 01:25:21,479
That's something we can't
get enough of in this business.

1112
01:25:25,028 --> 01:25:28,193
I'll admit since last we jawed...

1113
01:25:28,480 --> 01:25:30,686
my stomach's
been seizing up on me.

1114
01:25:30,782 --> 01:25:33,563
If the Dane's saying
we should double-cross you--

1115
01:25:33,659 --> 01:25:37,591
You double-cross once,
where's it all end?

1116
01:25:37,879 --> 01:25:40,469
An interesting ethical question.

1117
01:25:45,744 --> 01:25:48,717
I'll find the Dane,
talk to him,
straighten things out.

1118
01:25:49,005 --> 01:25:52,170
- Sure, talk to him.
Have a chat.
- I'll take care of it.

1119
01:25:52,266 --> 01:25:55,143
- Ask him if he's selling you out.
I'm sure he'll come clean.
- I'll take care of it.

1120
01:25:55,335 --> 01:25:58,596
- You're swimmin' in it.
- I said I'd take care of it!

1121
01:26:07,899 --> 01:26:11,160
-Johnny.

1122
01:26:11,255 --> 01:26:15,284
My chin's hanging out
right alongside yours.

1123
01:26:17,106 --> 01:26:20,271
I'd worry a lot less if
I thought you were worrying enough.

1124
01:26:24,682 --> 01:26:26,409
But I am, kid.

1125
01:26:30,053 --> 01:26:31,779
Christ.

1126
01:26:33,122 --> 01:26:35,328
Running things.

1127
01:26:45,302 --> 01:26:47,509
- Yeah?
I got your message.

1128
01:26:47,701 --> 01:26:50,578
Oh, Bernie. I had a dream
about you the other day.

1129
01:26:50,770 --> 01:26:53,935
- Yeah? A nightmare?
- On the contrary. Very sweet.

1130
01:26:54,222 --> 01:26:57,196
I dreamt you were
lying out at Miller's Crossing
with your face blown off.

1131
01:26:57,387 --> 01:27:00,552
You get a kick out of that?
- I was in stitches.

1132
01:27:00,840 --> 01:27:03,429
- It's Mink, isn't it?
- I came back.
He wasn't happy to see me.

1133
01:27:03,621 --> 01:27:05,348
- Can you beat that?
- Some friend.

1134
01:27:05,539 --> 01:27:07,362
Yeah. You know what
a nervous boy he was.

1135
01:27:07,362 --> 01:27:10,910
I figured you're a friend,
maybe you could use
some insurance.

1136
01:27:11,198 --> 01:27:13,020
Did Mink have a .22?

1137
01:27:15,130 --> 01:27:17,911
-He already ditched it. Why?
- After he shot Rug?

1138
01:27:18,007 --> 01:27:20,980
- Yeah. How'd you know?
- Doesn't matter.

1139
01:27:21,076 --> 01:27:25,488
- I've been thinking about
our deal. You can stick it
in your ear.  - Huh?

1140
01:27:25,680 --> 01:27:28,845
You don't have anything
on me that I don't have on you,
so I'm calling your bluff.

1141
01:27:29,132 --> 01:27:31,242
- Wait a minute.
- I'm pulling out
tomorrow morning.

1142
01:27:31,338 --> 01:27:34,695
You only have to decide
whether or not I leave behind
a message for Caspar...

1143
01:27:34,887 --> 01:27:36,613
that you're still around.

1144
01:27:36,805 --> 01:27:39,011
If you want me to keep
my mouth shut, it's gonna
cost you some dough.

1145
01:27:39,203 --> 01:27:41,600
I figure a thousand bucks
is reasonable, so I want two.

1146
01:27:41,696 --> 01:27:44,669
- In a pig's eye!
- I'm going out. I'll be back
at 4:00 this morning.

1147
01:27:44,957 --> 01:27:47,643
If you're not here at my place,
4:00, with the dough,

1148
01:27:47,835 --> 01:27:50,904
- Caspar's gonna be
looking for you tomorrow.
- Wait, wait, wait!

1149
01:27:58,481 --> 01:28:01,646
- Got any money?
- No.

1150
01:28:03,084 --> 01:28:05,290
Okay.

1151
01:28:19,101 --> 01:28:20,923
Third race tonight.

1152
01:28:21,019 --> 01:28:24,567
By the finish, Tailor Made
had a view of the field.

1153
01:28:24,855 --> 01:28:27,061
You oughta lay off
the ponies, Tom.

1154
01:28:33,486 --> 01:28:35,213
Okay.

1155
01:28:41,351 --> 01:28:44,612
Lazarre said he's sorry about this.
It's just getting out of hand.

1156
01:28:44,803 --> 01:28:46,627
Yeah.

1157
01:28:46,723 --> 01:28:48,545
He likes you, Tom.

1158
01:28:48,737 --> 01:28:51,038
He said we didn't have to
break anything.

1159
01:28:51,901 --> 01:28:53,916
It's okay.

1160
01:28:54,011 --> 01:28:56,409
Tell him there's
no hard feelings. Heh!

1161
01:28:56,601 --> 01:29:00,437
Christ, Tom...
he knows that.

1162
01:29:03,123 --> 01:29:05,137
Take care now.

1163
01:29:18,947 --> 01:29:20,769
- Tom Reagan.
- Yes, sir.

1164
01:29:20,865 --> 01:29:24,222
- Mr. Caspar's in the great room.
- Swell. Can you hold these?

1165
01:29:25,852 --> 01:29:27,675
Kid, what's the rumpus?

1166
01:29:27,866 --> 01:29:29,593
I got news.

1167
01:29:29,784 --> 01:29:32,661
Yeah. News at this end too.

1168
01:29:32,852 --> 01:29:35,154
My stomach's been
seizing up on me.

1169
01:29:35,250 --> 01:29:37,744
- Mink just told me that he--
- Eh?

1170
01:29:37,936 --> 01:29:41,196
- You talked to Mink?
- Yeah, on the phone.

1171
01:29:41,388 --> 01:29:44,265
The Dane wants you to think
that he's disappeared
so you can't talk to him,

1172
01:29:44,457 --> 01:29:47,239
- but he's been here in town.
- You sure it was Mink?

1173
01:29:47,431 --> 01:29:50,980
Yeah. See for yourself.
He's coming to my place,
4:00 this morning.

1174
01:29:51,267 --> 01:29:54,720
He's afraid of
a crossing with Dane.
He told me about the fix.

1175
01:29:54,912 --> 01:29:57,981
He says he'll sing for
a couple of grand skip money,
tell us everyone involved.

1176
01:29:58,269 --> 01:30:00,474
But you'd better take care
of the Dane tonight.

1177
01:30:00,666 --> 01:30:03,256
Mink says he's
coming after us tonight.

1178
01:30:09,202 --> 01:30:11,504
Leo's holed up
at Whiskey Nick's dump.

1179
01:30:11,696 --> 01:30:13,518
What? How do you know?

1180
01:30:13,518 --> 01:30:16,395
That ain't all we know, smart guy.

1181
01:30:17,642 --> 01:30:20,615
Recognize your playmate?

1182
01:30:24,643 --> 01:30:27,232
You thought I'd quit, huh? Uh-uh.

1183
01:30:27,424 --> 01:30:30,110
I followed you
this afternoon,

1184
01:30:30,397 --> 01:30:33,754
and I wondered why Einstein
would wanna talk to a gorilla.

1185
01:30:33,850 --> 01:30:37,111
So I grabbed the gorilla,
and I beat it out of him.

1186
01:30:37,398 --> 01:30:40,659
You give me a big guy
every time. They break easy.
Not like you.

1187
01:30:40,851 --> 01:30:44,016
Is there a point,
or are you just brushing up
on your small talk?

1188
01:30:44,304 --> 01:30:47,470
I like that.
Cool under fire.

1189
01:30:48,716 --> 01:30:50,539
I'm impressed.

1190
01:30:52,169 --> 01:30:55,526
The gorilla didn't know
whose stiff we found,
but I can fill that in.

1191
01:30:55,717 --> 01:30:58,499
You killed Mink,
you son of a bitch!

1192
01:30:59,746 --> 01:31:02,910
It was Mink,
you son of a bitch.

1193
01:31:03,198 --> 01:31:07,610
It was Mink, and by God,
I'll hear you say it.

1194
01:31:07,898 --> 01:31:10,103
Is this how you told Drop
his story?

1195
01:31:12,405 --> 01:31:14,515
Come here, bum.

1196
01:31:18,160 --> 01:31:21,133
I am gonna send you
to a deep, dark place,

1197
01:31:21,324 --> 01:31:23,914
and I am gonna have fun doing it.

1198
01:31:39,738 --> 01:31:41,561
Oof!.

1199
01:31:41,753 --> 01:31:46,549
You son of a bitch!
Son of a bitch!
You lousy son of a bitch!

1200
01:31:46,932 --> 01:31:50,385
If there's one thing
I can't stand,
it's a double-cross artist!

1201
01:31:52,879 --> 01:31:55,660
I had a theory
about this son of a bitch!

1202
01:31:59,880 --> 01:32:04,387
Shut up, you lousy
son of a bitch, or I'll give you
something to holler about!

1203
01:32:04,675 --> 01:32:07,552
Johnny, it's okay.
The Dane made him do it.
It's not important.

1204
01:32:07,840 --> 01:32:11,101
Then make him shut it!

1205
01:32:11,293 --> 01:32:14,841
And we do the same to Mink
this very same night!

1206
01:32:15,033 --> 01:32:17,718
We can't double-cross Mink.
He wants to spill the whole setup.

1207
01:32:17,910 --> 01:32:21,267
- I've never let
a son of a bitch walk.
- You've never crossed anyone.

1208
01:32:21,459 --> 01:32:24,624
4:00, my place. Mink's
coming in on his own hook,
so I promised him the money.

1209
01:32:24,911 --> 01:32:29,803
- Don't make me out
to be a liar.

1210
01:32:32,392 --> 01:32:34,694
Look at this, kid.

1211
01:32:36,420 --> 01:32:39,105
Something I try to teach
all my boys.

1212
01:32:48,409 --> 01:32:51,095
Always put one in the brain.

1213
01:33:12,290 --> 01:33:14,016
What's the rumpus?

1214
01:33:14,208 --> 01:33:17,469
I was just in the neighborhood
feeling a little daffy.

1215
01:33:17,757 --> 01:33:19,867
- What are you doing?
- Walking.

1216
01:33:19,963 --> 01:33:22,072
Don't let on more
than you have to.

1217
01:33:22,264 --> 01:33:23,991
In the rain.

1218
01:33:28,498 --> 01:33:30,320
Bernie's dead, isn't he?

1219
01:33:31,663 --> 01:33:34,540
- What makes you think that?
- That's no answer.

1220
01:33:39,144 --> 01:33:41,637
I can't tell you
anything yet.

1221
01:33:41,829 --> 01:33:44,515
No one really cares, do they?

1222
01:33:44,610 --> 01:33:49,407
- His friends
didn't really like him.
- He didn't like his friends.

1223
01:33:49,599 --> 01:33:52,572
You're someone to talk.
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

1224
01:33:52,859 --> 01:33:55,545
You got me
to tell you where he was,
and then you killed him.

1225
01:33:56,792 --> 01:33:58,710
I want to know why.

1226
01:33:58,806 --> 01:34:02,354
- What was in it for you?
- Nothing for me.

1227
01:34:06,766 --> 01:34:10,218
Giving up Bernie was
the only way I could see to
straighten things out for Leo.

1228
01:34:12,232 --> 01:34:14,918
I thought you said
you didn't care about Leo.

1229
01:34:15,110 --> 01:34:18,466
I said we were through.
It's not the same thing.

1230
01:34:18,754 --> 01:34:21,056
I don't understand.
I don't care.

1231
01:34:21,248 --> 01:34:24,317
I don't care what reasons you had
or you thought you had.

1232
01:34:24,413 --> 01:34:26,810
He's still alive.

1233
01:34:28,920 --> 01:34:30,838
You expect me to believe you?

1234
01:34:36,017 --> 01:34:37,839
No.

1235
01:34:41,004 --> 01:34:43,882
That's you all over, Tom.

1236
01:34:44,169 --> 01:34:46,376
A lie and no heart.

1237
01:35:03,543 --> 01:35:05,366
Oh--

1238
01:35:12,654 --> 01:35:14,573
It isn't easy, is it, Verna?

1239
01:35:29,630 --> 01:35:33,274
But before
you even think about doing
that, you gotta towel down.

1240
01:35:33,466 --> 01:35:38,549
So you towel down first
with a hot towel,
as hot as you can stand.

1241
01:35:38,741 --> 01:35:41,139
Put the razor
in cold water, not hot,

1242
01:35:41,330 --> 01:35:43,824
because metal
does what in cold?

1243
01:35:44,112 --> 01:35:48,141
- I don't know,Johnny.
- That's why I'm telling you!
It contracts.

1244
01:35:50,347 --> 01:35:53,895
That way you get
a first-class shave every time.

1245
01:35:54,183 --> 01:35:56,005
Okay,Johnny.

1246
01:35:58,595 --> 01:36:00,513
Ain't it the life though?

1247
01:36:04,061 --> 01:36:07,322
Hello, Sal. You can dangle.

1248
01:36:07,610 --> 01:36:12,021
Hello, Tom. You sure?
You don't look so hot.

1249
01:36:12,309 --> 01:36:13,940
I'm okay.

1250
01:36:16,625 --> 01:36:18,639
I'll drive him home.

1251
01:37:09,087 --> 01:37:11,676
Mr. Reagan, there were shots.

1252
01:37:11,868 --> 01:37:14,553
Go down to the drug store
and call the police.

1253
01:37:16,280 --> 01:37:18,965
You'd better stay there
till the officers arrive.

1254
01:37:20,116 --> 01:37:22,034
Will my cats be all right?

1255
01:37:22,130 --> 01:37:24,048
Yeah, they'll be fine.

1256
01:38:13,824 --> 01:38:16,606
I get it. You set me up.

1257
01:38:16,702 --> 01:38:19,483
Anything to avoid
a little dirty work yourself, huh?

1258
01:38:21,593 --> 01:38:24,662
How'd you know he'd get it
and not me? Or didn't you care?

1259
01:38:24,950 --> 01:38:27,251
I figured you'd come early
looking for blood.

1260
01:38:27,443 --> 01:38:30,128
He wouldn't, so you'd likely
have the drop on him.

1261
01:38:31,759 --> 01:38:35,691
You're right.
The chump never knew what hit him.

1262
01:38:35,787 --> 01:38:39,048
But if you knew
I'd come to kill you,
how do you know I won't still?

1263
01:38:39,240 --> 01:38:42,021
There's nothing in it
for you now.

1264
01:38:42,213 --> 01:38:44,899
With him dead, you and me
got nothing on each other.

1265
01:38:45,954 --> 01:38:48,256
- Let me have the gun.
- Why?

1266
01:38:48,448 --> 01:38:50,749
Pin this on the Dane.

1267
01:38:50,845 --> 01:38:53,627
Neither of us want him
walking around after this.

1268
01:38:53,818 --> 01:38:57,271
The cops'll be Leo's now.
They won't care what
they hang the Dane for.

1269
01:38:57,463 --> 01:38:59,285
I guess that's true,

1270
01:38:59,477 --> 01:39:03,505
if you don't mind keeping
the gun that killed Caspar
and Mink.

1271
01:39:04,656 --> 01:39:06,862
Why did Mink
shoot Rug anyway?

1272
01:39:07,053 --> 01:39:08,876
I don't know.
It was just a mix-up.

1273
01:39:09,067 --> 01:39:11,273
Here.

1274
01:39:14,055 --> 01:39:17,507
- So you're gonna say
the Dane did this?
- Sure.

1275
01:39:17,699 --> 01:39:20,288
Mink thought Rug
was tailing him.

1276
01:39:20,480 --> 01:39:22,878
You know Mink. Hysterical.
Skin full of hop,
head full of boogeymen.

1277
01:39:23,070 --> 01:39:27,194
Comes home crying one day,
saying he had to pop
one of the Dane's spies.

1278
01:39:27,481 --> 01:39:30,742
Rug was tailing Verna,
not Mink. Mink just
happened to be with her.

1279
01:39:30,934 --> 01:39:32,756
Funny, ain't it?

1280
01:39:32,852 --> 01:39:35,825
Mink was terrified
the Dane'd find out me and him
were jungled up together.

1281
01:39:36,017 --> 01:39:38,798
I bet you kept him
worried about that to
keep him under your thumb.

1282
01:39:39,086 --> 01:39:41,292
Yeah, so what?
Scratch, huh?

1283
01:39:41,484 --> 01:39:43,881
A little bonus.

1284
01:39:43,977 --> 01:39:47,143
- Why did Mink take Rug's hair?
- Beats me. The kid was dizzy.

1285
01:39:47,335 --> 01:39:51,171
Fifty-fifty on the dough?
Or maybe I should get more,
since I did the deed.

1286
01:39:53,761 --> 01:39:56,350
Okay, you keep it.
I want you to have it.

1287
01:40:02,967 --> 01:40:07,378
Bernie... we can't pin this
on the Dane.

1288
01:40:07,570 --> 01:40:12,941
- Why not?
- Because the Dane's already
dead halfway across town.

1289
01:40:13,229 --> 01:40:16,202
- What the hell
are you talking about?
- Eddie Dane is dead.

1290
01:40:16,490 --> 01:40:18,216
It's gotta be you.

1291
01:40:19,846 --> 01:40:22,052
I mean, it was your gun.

1292
01:40:24,354 --> 01:40:28,190
What is this?
What the hell are you talking about?

1293
01:40:28,478 --> 01:40:30,684
You--

1294
01:40:30,875 --> 01:40:34,136
You took my gun.
It's just your word against mine.

1295
01:40:37,493 --> 01:40:39,507
Not necessarily.

1296
01:40:40,562 --> 01:40:42,576
Are you crazy?

1297
01:40:42,768 --> 01:40:45,838
We're square.
You said it yourself.
We got nothing on each other.

1298
01:40:46,030 --> 01:40:48,236
Yep.

1299
01:40:48,331 --> 01:40:52,455
So what's in it for you?
There's no angle.

1300
01:40:52,647 --> 01:40:55,333
You can't just shoot me
like that.

1301
01:40:58,785 --> 01:41:02,046
Jesus Christ,
it don't make sense.

1302
01:41:04,252 --> 01:41:06,074
Tommy--

1303
01:41:07,992 --> 01:41:10,390
Tommy!

1304
01:41:12,116 --> 01:41:13,938
Look in your heart.

1305
01:41:16,432 --> 01:41:18,926
- Look in your heart.
- What heart?

1306
01:42:02,276 --> 01:42:04,194
Tad? It's Tom.

1307
01:42:05,633 --> 01:42:08,414
Tell Lazarre
I got his money.

1308
01:42:08,606 --> 01:42:10,428
Yeah, all of it.

1309
01:42:10,620 --> 01:42:13,305
I wanna place a bet
on tonight's fight.

1310
01:42:18,197 --> 01:42:19,923
- They set you up downstairs?
- How's that?

1311
01:42:20,115 --> 01:42:22,129
A little hooch, whatever?

1312
01:42:22,225 --> 01:42:24,910
Thanks for coming, Tom.
Leo's real anxious to see you.

1313
01:42:25,102 --> 01:42:27,020
Yeah, I happened to be near.

1314
01:42:29,322 --> 01:42:32,295
Well, uh, actually this might
not be the best time.

1315
01:42:32,487 --> 01:42:35,172
- Who's he got in there?
- O'Doole and the mayor.

1316
01:42:35,364 --> 01:42:39,680
- I'll try again.
- They're planting the sheeny
tomorrow. You could stop by.

1317
01:43:07,877 --> 01:43:11,234
- Big turnout.
- Drop dead.

1318
01:43:11,426 --> 01:43:13,344
She's under a lot of strain.

1319
01:43:13,536 --> 01:43:16,796
- Yeah, well, at least
she didn't hit me.

1320
01:43:16,892 --> 01:43:20,057
Glad you came, Tommy.

1321
01:43:20,249 --> 01:43:23,797
- I guess, uh-- Huh?
- She's taking the car.

1322
01:43:28,401 --> 01:43:31,278
- I guess we're walkin'.
- Guess we are.

1323
01:43:36,169 --> 01:43:38,183
We're, uh--
We're getting married.

1324
01:43:40,965 --> 01:43:43,266
Congratulations.

1325
01:43:43,458 --> 01:43:48,255
Funny thing is, she asked me to
tie the knot. I guess you're
not supposed to say that.

1326
01:43:48,542 --> 01:43:51,132
- It doesn't matter.
Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1327
01:43:52,666 --> 01:43:55,352
Hell, Tom, why didn't you
tell me what you were up to?

1328
01:43:55,448 --> 01:43:57,749
I thought you'd
really gone over.

1329
01:43:57,845 --> 01:44:01,202
Not that I didn't deserve it,
but you could've told me.

1330
01:44:01,394 --> 01:44:04,655
Telling you would only
have queered things if it--

1331
01:44:04,942 --> 01:44:07,628
There just wasn't any point.

1332
01:44:07,819 --> 01:44:09,546
I can see that.

1333
01:44:11,080 --> 01:44:13,862
It was a smart play all around.

1334
01:44:14,053 --> 01:44:16,835
I guess you know I'm grateful.

1335
01:44:17,026 --> 01:44:18,849
No need.

1336
01:44:20,575 --> 01:44:23,164
Heh!
I guess you picked
that fight with me...

1337
01:44:23,356 --> 01:44:26,521
just to check yourself
in with Caspar.

1338
01:44:26,617 --> 01:44:30,166
I don't know.
Do you always know
why you do things, Leo?

1339
01:44:30,453 --> 01:44:32,180
Sure I do.

1340
01:44:34,290 --> 01:44:36,879
- It was a smart play.
- Fine.

1341
01:44:40,044 --> 01:44:43,305
Jesus, Tom, I'd do anything
if you'd work for me again.

1342
01:44:43,593 --> 01:44:46,663
I know I've made
some bonehead plays,
I know I can be pigheaded,

1343
01:44:46,758 --> 01:44:49,156
but, damn it, so can you.

1344
01:44:49,252 --> 01:44:53,472
I need you.
Things can be the way they were.

1345
01:44:53,760 --> 01:44:55,870
I know it.
I just know it.

1346
01:44:55,965 --> 01:45:00,185
As for you and Verna,
well, I understand.

1347
01:45:00,473 --> 01:45:03,062
You're both young.

1348
01:45:03,158 --> 01:45:05,268
